etymologies: late Middle English; earliest use found in Promptorium Parvulorum. From empt + -ing

notes.text: Later examples may be errors for emptying.

definitions: In plural, especially in form emptins. A type of yeast deriving from the process of fermentation, typically used in baking. More generally: yeast of any type; a preparation containing yeast or another raising agent. Compare "emptying". Now chiefly historical.
